related_questions.question: What is a brad for crafts?
related_questions.snippet: Brads are two-pronged paper fasteners, usually with a decorative top. They can be used in card-making and scrapbooking, and are decorative and functional. Brads can add moving elements to your paper crafts when two pieces are fastened together.

related_questions.question: Who invented brads?
related_questions.snippet: George W. McGill (1843-1917), an inventor and patent attorney (how convenient!) invented the first of many metal fasteners in 1866.
